Dialogue: 10,0:00:15.40,0:00:20.02,Default,,400,0,0,,{\i1}Sometimes at night, when I happen to catch the scent of flowers,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:20.02,0:00:22.98,Default,,400,0,0,,{\i1}I feel as though I'm about to remember something I've forgotten.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:24.39,0:00:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaoru, what's taking you{ so long}?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:27.20,0:00:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, we should head home.{Keep this. Nota bene: Although "Come on" has long since been accepted as an interjection in anime subtitles (and treated as such at the beginnings of sentences), "Come" is less common but not altogether incorrect. If "Come on" is to be accepted, so, too, should "Come" be. Therefore, during this episode, I'll treat instances of the sentence-beginning "Come" as interjections.}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:29.13,0:00:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Oh, right.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:36.09,0:00:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I can never seem to remember
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.36,0:00:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that familiar, yet strangely terrifying, something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.69,0:00:54.70,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\fad(2000,0)\an7\bord0\blur0.6\p1\c&H42E9EF&\pos(-2,68)\fscx600\fscy90}m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100
